					Post by: <b>Stephen Gornick</b> on <b>November 09, 2012, 07:30:18 AM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;"><div class="quoteheader"><a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=123445.msg1325632#msg1325632">Quote from: J.Socal on November 09, 2012, 07:17:50 AM</a></div><div class="quote">Latest Bitcoin-Qt version: 0.7.1 ...I have v0.6.2-beta&nbsp; ...Is it recommended to upgrade it every few months?If so,whats the process?<br /></div><br />Each of the Bitcoin.org clients are backward compatible.&nbsp; You simply can run setup on top of an existing installation.&nbsp; With linux, you can simply overwrite the existing executable with the latest.<br /><br />The wallet.dat is not touched during the installation process.&nbsp; It is still advisable that you make a backup of the wallet.dat from right before updating though.<br /></div>
